goals.visualization: bar chart of origin and destination
goals.rationale: This tells us which airports are the busiest and have the highest number of flights.

goals.question: What is the distribution of flight dates?
goals.rationale: This tells us how many flights were scheduled on each day and if there are any patterns or trends in flight scheduling.

goals.question: What is the relationship between flight delay and distance?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of delay and distance
goals.rationale: This tells us if there is any correlation between flight delay and distance, and if longer flights are more likely to be delayed.

```python
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import statsmodels.api as sm
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['delay'].plot.hist(bins=20)
    plt.xlabel('Delay (minutes)')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flight delays?', wrap=True)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

```python
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.boxplot(data['distance'])
    plt.ylabel('Distance (miles)')
    median_distance = data['distance'].median()
    plt.axhline(y=median_distance, color='r', linestyle='--', label=f'Median Distance: {median_distance:.2f}')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the average distance of flights?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

```python
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    origin_counts = data['origin'].value_counts()
    destination_counts = data['destination'].value_counts()
    total_counts = origin_counts.add(destination_counts, fill_value=0).sort_values(ascending=False)
    
    total_counts.plot(kind='bar')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("Which airports have the highest number of flights?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
```

```python
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='ignore')
    data_count = data['date'].value_counts().sort_index()
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.plot(data_count.index, data_count.values)
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the distribution of flight dates?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```
